{
  "texts": [
    "C.4 Performance Stability of ISACIt is known that an initial random seed (X T) significantly impact the compositional image generation performance [68].",
    "To see its impact, we report the stability of base models and ISAC across initial random seeds in Tab. 16.",
    "As IntraCompBench already consider the seed variance by generating 10 images from a single prompt and 10 different seeds, we measured the variance with T2I-CompBench [13] Numeracy task.",
    "Importantly, ISAC reduces standard deviation by approximately 3-4 times, clearly demonstrating ISAC's consistent improvement across diverse prompts and initializations.",
    "Fig. 22 qualitatively shows this stability as well."
  ]
}